    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-07T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-07T11:00:00-05:00" n="408"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_EAC1"
                    >EAC</gloss>/7–745: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 408<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_WJG2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent—niact</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-07T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 7, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6863. <hi rend="smallcaps">Comea</hi> 327. Re final <gloss target="#t_para1"
                        >para</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_mytel1">mytel</gloss> 6856, July 7<note n="1" xml:id="d408fn1">
                        <ref target="#d407">Document No. 407</ref>.</note> repeated <persName
                        corresp="#p_MRE1">Murphy</persName> as 20.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> and French <gloss target="#t_EAC1">EAC</gloss>
                    delegations have considered Soviet proposal of July 6 re omission final sentence
                    report accompanying agreement French zone in Germany. Both delegations have
                    recommended their Govts agree this omission. They feel more important conclude
                    agreement and leave open question of procedure for determining French area in
                    Berlin than to force decision in <gloss target="#t_EAC1">EAC</gloss> at this
                    point.</p>
                <p>Sent <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> as 6863; repeated <persName
                        corresp="#p_MRE1">Murphy</persName> as 24 from <persName corresp="#p_WJG2"
                        >Winant</persName>.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> and French <gloss target="#t_EAC1">EAC</gloss>
                    delegations expect final word this point Mon morning from their Govts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJG2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
